<p><b>Bill Forsyth</b> (born 29 July 1946) is a <a href="Scotland" title="Scotland">Scottish</a> <a href="Film_director" title="Film director">film director</a> and writer best known for his films <i><a href="Gregory's_Girl" title="Gregory's Girl">Gregory's Girl</a></i> (1981), <i><a href="Local_Hero" title="Local Hero">Local Hero</a></i> (1983), and <i><a href="Comfort_and_Joy_(1984_film)" title="Comfort and Joy (1984 film)">Comfort and Joy</a></i> (1984), as well as his commitment to national film-making.<sup id="cite_ref-imdb_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-imdb-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<table id="toc" class="toc">
